headline: Starbucks (SBUX) Is Up 8.2% After Turnaround-Focused Q1 Results And New Growth Initiatives - What's Changed
summary: In late January 2026, Starbucks reported first-quarter revenue of US$9,915.1 million, up from US$9,397.8 million a year earlier, but net income fell to US$293.3 million as the company continued to invest in its turnaround.
